page.title: 01River Test Estuary Gazetteer
page.content: The Domesday Block 04360111 surrounds the estuary of the River Test. The North Eastern corner consists mainly of l930s privately owned housing and some light industry. Towards the West is the Millbrook Housing Estate and the upper tidal reaches of the River Test with surburban Totton in the extreme West. There is an area of dockland along the North bank of the Test. This is bordered to the North by the Southampton_Bournemouth railway line, running East/West with an industrial estate between it and the Millbrook Road (the western entrance to Southampton). South of the river is a muddy tidal coastland with rough pasture and farmland beyond. Eling village is the focal point of the mid west with forest land in the south west corner.
